This paper involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques to uncover linguistic universals. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper uses probabilistic models, which suggests it could also belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves knowledge base population, which could place it in the sub-category of Cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques, which could place it in the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
